<section id="overview">

<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>
I am a medical doctor from Bangladesh currently pursuing a Master's in Health Informatics at Karolinska Institutet and Stockholm University. My work focuses on the intersection of clinical medicine, epidemiology, and digital health systems.
</p>

<p>
I have over eight years of experience in disease surveillance, clinical research, and health system strengthening. My work includes national health surveillance programs, randomized clinical trials, and digital health data systems.
</p>

<p>
My goal is to use health informatics and data science to improve public health decision making and healthcare system performance in low and middle income countries.
</p>

